## PHASE 4 — Post-Migration Checklist

Generated when all waves are complete (or user skips remaining items):

```
Pre-cutover
  □ Verify all Hetzner servers are running and reachable (agent can check)
  □ Run your test suite against Hetzner endpoints
  □ Verify database row counts match source (run: SELECT COUNT(*) on both)
  □ Test authentication end-to-end (if Cognito → Keycloak migration done)
  □ Confirm SSL certificates active and auto-renewing (Let's Encrypt)
  □ Review Hetzner Firewall rules against your security requirements

DNS Cutover (do not rush this)
  □ Lower TTL to 60s on all relevant DNS records — do this 24h before cutover
  □ Update A/AAAA records to point to Hetzner IPs
  □ Monitor error rates for 30 minutes post-cutover
  □ Keep AWS resources running for 72h post-cutover as rollback option

Post-Cutover
  □ Confirm AWS traffic has dropped to zero (check ALB request count)
  □ Update monitoring dashboards to point to Hetzner endpoints
  □ Archive AWS configuration (export Terraform state, save configs)

Cleanup — wait 30 days, then:
  □ Delete AWS resources in reverse wave order (wave 4 first, wave 1 last)
  □ Revoke Lens IAM role (no longer needed once off AWS)
  □ Close AWS account if no longer needed
  □ Run a Lens re-scan against the Hetzner account to confirm improved score
```

