## PHASE 6 — Database Schema

```
guide_blueprint table:
  id, userId, organizationId, label
  sourceCloud, targetCloud
  lensScore, glanceExportId
  status ("draft" | "ready" | "in_progress" | "complete")
  migrationProgress (int, 0–100)
  networkPlan (JSONB)
  gapAnalysis (JSONB)         // gap decisions per resource
  costEstimate (JSONB)
  createdAt, updatedAt

guide_resource_mapping table:
  id, blueprintId, userId
  sourceResourceId, sourceService, sourceName, sourceConfig (JSONB)
  targetService, targetName, targetSpec (JSONB)
  equivalenceType, equivalenceNotes
  migrationWave, migrationEffort
  migrationStatus ("pending" | "in_progress" | "complete" | "skipped")
  hetznerResourceId (int, nullable)   // set after validation confirms it exists
  hetznerResourceType (text, nullable)
  validatedAt (timestamp, nullable)   // when agent last confirmed it exists
  staticGuide, customInstructions
  createdAt, updatedAt

guide_session table:
  id, blueprintId, userId
  currentWave, currentStep
  status ("active" | "paused" | "complete")
  messages (JSONB — last 50 messages for context)
  stepChecklist (JSONB — per-guide step completion per resource)
  createdAt, updatedAt

  Note: Hetzner API token is NOT stored here or anywhere in the DB.
  It is held in an encrypted server-side session store (Redis) for the
  duration of the browser session only. It expires when the session ends.
  This is non-negotiable.

guide_validation_log table:
  id, sessionId, resourceMappingId, userId
  toolName                        // which read tool was called
  hetznerResponseSummary (JSONB)  // sanitised result (IDs, status — no secrets)
  outcome ("confirmed" | "not_found" | "config_mismatch" | "error")
  validatedAt
```

